The paper deals with the analysis of social media data, specifically Twitter, and focuses on demographic information, which is relevant to social informatics (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) and Bayesian classification (cs.CYBER) in their methodology. Finally, the paper touches on privacy and child protection implications, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) or social computing (cs.SOC).
